{{Use British English|date=June 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Ben Chilwell | image = France - England U19, 20150331 14.JPG | image_size = 200 | caption = Chilwell playing for [[England national under-19 football team|England U19]] in 2015 | fullname = Benjamin James Chilwell<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/84136 |title=Squads for 2016/17 Premier League confirmed |publisher=Premier League |date=1 September 2016 |accessdate=2 June 2017}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1996|12|21}}<ref name=11v11>{{cite web |url=https://www.11v11.com/players/ben-chilwell-249895/ |title=Ben Chilwell |website=11v11.com |publisher=AFS Enterprises |accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref> | birth_place = [[Milton Keynes]], England | height = {{convert|1.78|m|order=flip}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/benjamin-chilwell/383419/ |title=B. Chilwell |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |accessdate=20 December 2017}}</ref> | position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] | currentclub = [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] | clubnumber = 3 | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = Woburn Lions<ref name="FAMyStory">{{cite web |title=Ben Chilwell: My story |url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2018/oct/12/ben-chilwell-my-story-121018 |website=The FA |accessdate=16 October 2018}}</ref> | youthyears2 = | youthclubs2 = Bletchley Youth | youthyears3 = –2010 | youthclubs3 = [[Rushden & Diamonds F.C.|Rushden & Diamonds]] | youthyears4 = 2010–2015 | youthclubs4 = [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] | years1 = 2015– | clubs1 = [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] | caps1 = 65 | goals1 = 1 | years2 = 2015–2016 | clubs2 = → [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] (loan) | caps2 = 8 | goals2 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2014 | nationalteam1 = [[England national under-18 football team|England U18]] | nationalcaps1 = 3 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalyears2 = 2014–2015 | nationalteam2 = [[England national under-19 football team|England U19]] | nationalcaps2 = 6 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | nationalyears3 = 2015 | nationalteam3 = [[England national under-20 football team|England U20]] | nationalcaps3 = 3 | nationalgoals3 = 1 | nationalyears4 = 2016– | nationalteam4 = [[England national under-21 football team|England U21]] | nationalcaps4 = 10 | nationalgoals4 = 0 | nationalyears5 = 2018– | nationalteam5 = [[England national football team|England]] | nationalcaps5 = 6 | nationalgoals5 = 0 | club-update = 00:01, 23 March 2019 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = 00:01, 23 March 2019 (UTC) }} '''Benjamin James Chilwell''' (born 21 December 1996) is an English professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for {{English football updater|LeicestC}} club [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] and the [[England national football team|English national team]].
==Club career== Chilwell was born in [[Milton Keynes]], Buckinghamshire and attended [[Redborne Upper School and Community College]].<ref name=11v11/><ref>{{cite web |title=News from Summer 2016 |url=https://www.redbornecommunitycollege.com/page/?title=News+from+Summer+2016&pid=89 |website=Redborne Upper School |accessdate=11 January 2019}}</ref> He is a product of the [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] academy and won their Academy Player of the Year award at the end of the 2014–15 season.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lcfc.com/news/article/esteban-cambiasso-named-leicester-city-player-of-the-year-2461984.aspx |title=Esteban Cambiasso Named Leicester City Player of the Year |publisher=Leicester City F.C.}}</ref>
After featuring for the club in pre-season under new manager [[Claudio Ranieri]], Chilwell was given the number 30 shirt ahead of the 2015–16 season. He made his professional debut on 27 October 2015 in the club's [[EFL Cup|League Cup]] match against [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]]. Chilwell played the entire match as Leicester lost 5–4 on penalties following a 1–1 draw after extra time.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/10/27/england/league-cup/hull-city-afc/leicester-city-fc/2159964 |title=Hull City vs. Leicester City – 27 October 2015 |publisher=Soccerway |accessdate=27 October 2015}}</ref>
On 19 November 2015, Chilwell joined [[EFL Championship|Championship]] side [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] on a youth loan until 3 January 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.examiner.co.uk/sport/football/news/huddersfield-town-complete-loan-signing-10467540 |title=Huddersfield Town complete loan signing of Leicester City left-back Ben Chilwell |first=Doug |last=Thomson |date=19 November 2015}}</ref> He made his debut in the 2–0 home loss to [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] nine days later.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Thomson |first1=Doug |title=Defeat by Middlesbrough took gloss off League debut of Huddersfield Town's on-loan Leicester City left-back Ben Chilwell |url=https://www.examiner.co.uk/sport/football/news/defeat-middlesbrough-took-gloss-league-10520419 |accessdate=16 September 2018 |work=The Huddersfield Daily Examiner |date=29 November 2015}}</ref>
On 28 July 2016, Chilwell signed a new contract with the club until 2021.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ben Chilwell: Highly Rated Youngster Signs Long-Term Leicester City Contract |url=http://www.lcfc.com/news/article/2016-17/ben-chilwell-highly-rated-youngster-signs-long-term-leicester-city-contract-3213190.aspx |publisher=lcfc.com |accessdate=28 July 2016}}</ref> On 26 December 2016, in the [[2016–17 Premier League|2016–17]] season, he made his [[Premier League]] debut in a 0–2 home defeat to [[Everton F.C.|Everton]]. Chilwell received praise for his performance.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38361078 |title=Leicester City 0–2 Everton |date=27 December 2016 |publisher=BBC}}</ref> He made 19 total appearances across the campaign, including two in the [[UEFA Champions League]], and scored his first career goal on 18 May 2017 in a 6–1 home loss to [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Rostance |first1=Tom |title=Leicester City 1&ndash;6 Tottenham Hotspur |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39879805 |accessdate=16 September 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=18 May 2017}}</ref>
Chilwell was sent off on 13 January 2018 for two yellow cards within five minutes of each other in a goalless draw at [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Chowdhury |first1=Saj |title=Chelsea 0&ndash;0 Leicester City |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42587969 |accessdate=16 September 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=13 January 2018}}</ref>
==International career== Along with his Leicester clubmate [[Demarai Gray]], Chilwell was called up from the [[England national under-21 football team|under-21 side]] to the full [[England national football team|England]] squad in September 2018 for a [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] match against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Ben Chilwell and Demarai Gray added to England squad for Switzerland friendly |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45466420 |publisher=BBC Sport |accessdate=10 September 2018 |date=9 September 2018}}</ref> He made his debut in this match on 11 September, as a 79th-minute substitute for [[Danny Rose (footballer, born 1990)|Danny Rose]] in a 1–0 home win.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45404026 |title=England 1–0 Switzerland |first=Phil |last=McNulty |publisher=BBC Sport |date=11 September 2018 |accessdate=11 September 2018}}</ref> Upon taking to the pitch in the match at the [[King Power Stadium]] he became the first England player to debut at his club ground since [[Paul Scholes]] at [[Old Trafford]] in 1997.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Tanner |first1=Rob |title=England's return to Leicester City showcases the progress the club has made in the last 15 years |url=https://www.leicestermercury.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/englands-return-leicester-city-showcases-1994798 |accessdate=14 September 2018 |work=Leicester Mercury |date=11 September 2018}}</ref> Chilwell made his first start on 12 October in a 0–0 draw away to [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] in the [[2018–19 UEFA Nations League A|UEFA Nations League A]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45755081 |title=Croatia 0–0 England |first=Phil |last=McNulty |publisher=BBC Sport |date=12 October 2018 |accessdate=12 October 2018}}</ref>
==Personal life== Chilwell's father is from [[New Zealand]], and emigrated to England in 1993 three years prior to Chilwell's birth.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/dec/07/ben-chilwell-aim-to-be-one-of-englands-best-ever-left-backs-leicester-city |title=Ben Chilwell: ‘My aim is to be one of England’s best ever left-backs’ &#124; Football |publisher=The Guardian |date=1970-01-01 |accessdate=2018-12-08}}</ref><ref name=FAMyStory></ref>
