'''Çağlar Söyüncü''' ({{IPA-tr|ˈtʃaːlaɾ sœˈjyndʒy}}; born 23 May 1996) is a Turkish professional [[Association football|footballer]], who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[Premier League]] side [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] and the [[Turkey national football team|Turkish national team]].
Joining SC Freiburg in [[List of German football transfers summer 2016|2016 Bundesliga summer transfer window]], he is the first Turkish footballer who made a transfer to [[Bundesliga]] directly from [[TFF First League]], the second highest professional level football league of Turkey.<ref name="Al Jazeera: Bundesliga transfer">{{cite web |url=http://www.aljazeera.com.tr/haber/1-ligden-yurt-disina-ilk-transfer |title=1. Lig'den yurt dışına ilk transfer |publisher=[[Al Jazeera Türk]] |author= |date=24 May 2016 |accessdate=6 October 2016 |language=tr}}</ref>
Making his senior national team debut in 2016, Söyüncü is the first [[Altınordu S.K.]] player called up to Turkey national football team after 78 years, since [[Sait Altınordu]], the iconic player of the club, was selected in 1937.<ref name="National Team Debut TFF">{{cite news |title=İzmir'in son gururu: Çağlar Söyüncü |url=http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=286&ftxtID=24983&1317pg=12 |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation|TFF]] |date=29 April 2016 |accessdate=8 October 2016 |language=Turkish |archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl=no}}</ref> He is also the first player called up to national team from any İzmir-based football clubs since 1997.
==Club career==
===Altınordu S.K=== During the 2015–2016 season he was linked with [[Beşiktaş J.K.]], [[Galatasaray S.K.]] and [[Sevilla FC]] but 20 years old Turkish national selected the Bundesliga because he thought it was better choice for his career and his improvement<ref name="Confession about Çağlar Söyüncü">{{cite news |title=Çağlar Söyüncü için itiraf:Beşiktaş ve Sevilla |url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/caglar-soyuncu-icin-itiraf--besiktas-2248697-skorerhaber/ |publisher=[[Milliyet]] |date=20 May 2016 |accessdate=17 March 2017 |language=Turkish|}}</ref>
===SC Freiburg=== On 24 May 2016, Söyüncü joined German side [[SC Freiburg]], which was promoted to the top flight competition of Germany for the [[2016–17 Bundesliga|2016–17 season]].<ref name="SC Freiburg Transfer 1">{{cite web |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/2bundesliga/vereine/652549/artikel_offiziell_-soeyuencue-schlaegt-im-breisgau-auf.html# |title=Offiziell: Söyüncü schlägt im Breisgau auf |publisher=[[Kicker (sports magazine)|Kicker]] |author= |date=24 May 2016 |accessdate=6 October 2016 |language=de}}</ref><ref name="SC Freiburg Transfer 2">{{cite web |url=http://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/noblsp-sc-freiburg-sign-turkey-defender-caglar-soyuncu.jsp |title=Freiburg sign Turkey defender Caglar Söyüncü |publisher=www.bundesliga.com |author= |date=24 May 2016 |accessdate=8 October 2016 |language=en}}</ref> He made his Bundesliga debut on week 1 encounter away against [[Hertha Berlin]] which ended 2–1 for Berlin outfit, on 28 August 2016.<ref name="Bundesliga Debut">{{cite news |title=Çağlar Söyüncü Freiburg ile ilk maçına çıktı |url=http://www.fanatik.com.tr/2016/08/28/caglar-soyuncu-freiburg-ile-ilk-macina-cikti-1250016 |publisher=[[Fanatik]] |date=28 August 2016 |accessdate=8 October 2016 |language=Turkish |archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl=no}}</ref> He was linked with [[Lille OSC]], [[AS Roma]], and [[Villarreal CF]] during the mid-season transfer window of 2016–17 season.<ref name="Four Four Two Turkish Edition: 2016–17 winter transfer window">{{cite web |url=http://fourfourtwo.com.tr/2017/02/02/%C3%A7a%C4%9Flar-s%C3%B6y%C3%BCnc%C3%BCn%C3%BCn-y%C4%B1ld%C4%B1z%C4%B1-parl%C4%B1yor/ |title=Çağlar Söyüncü’nün yıldızı parlıyor |publisher=[[Four Four Two|Four Four Two Turkish Edition]] |author= |date=2 February 2017 |accessdate=9 February 2017 |language=tr}}</ref> [[Manchester City F.C|Manchester City]] was also reported to be interested in Söyüncü.<ref name="Man City link">{{cite news |title=Guardiola'nın hedefindeki Türk: Çağlar Söyüncü |url=http://www.fanatik.com.tr/2017/02/07/guardiola-nin-hedefindeki-turk-caglar-soyuncu-1276711 |publisher=[[Fanatik]] |date=8 February 2017 |accessdate=9 February 2017 |language=Turkish |archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl=no}}</ref>
===Leicester City=== On 9 August 2018 Söyüncü joined [[Premier League]] side [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] on a five year contract, subject to a successful [[work permit]] application.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lcfc.com/news/799283/leicester-city-agree-alar-sync-transfer/press-release |title=Leicester City Agree Çağlar Söyüncü Transfer |publisher=Leicester City F.C. |date=9 August 2018 |accessdate=9 August 2018}}</ref>
==International career==
===Senior=== In November 2015, he was called up to [[Turkey national football team]] by coach [[Fatih Terim]], following the injury of central defender [[Serdar Aziz]].<ref name=NationalTeamCallUp1>{{cite news |title=Hedefim kalıcı olmak |url=http://www.haberturk.com/spor/futbol/haber/1153662-hedefim-kalici-olmak |publisher=[[Habertürk]] |date=15 November 2015 |accessdate=17 November 2015 |language=Turkish |archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name=NationalTeamCallUp2>{{cite news |title=Terim'den sürpriz davet! |url=http://www.ntvspor.net/haber/futbol/142952/terimden-surpriz-davet |publisher=[[NTV Spor]] |date=14 November 2015 |accessdate=22 November 2015 |language=Turkish |archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl=no}}</ref> On 17 November 2015 Söyüncü was a reserve for the a friendly game against [[Greece national football team|Greece]] but stayed on the bench and did not actually get a chance to play.<ref name=TurkeyGreece171120152>{{cite news |title=Türkiye 0–0 Yunanistan |url=http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=24117 |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation|TFF]] |date=17 November 2015 |accessdate=22 November 2015 |language=Turkish |archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl=no}}</ref> On 18 March 2016, he was called to national squad for friendly games against [[Sweden national football team|Sweden]] and [[Austria national football team|Austria]], to be held on 24 March 2016 in Antalya, Turkey and on 29 March in Austria, respectively.<ref name="Friendlies: Sweden and Austria, 2016 [1]">{{cite news |title=A Milli Takım'ın İsveç ve Avusturya maçları aday kadrosu ve programı |url=http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=24731 |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation|TFF]] |date=18 March 2016 |accessdate=19 March 2016 |language=Turkish |archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="Friendlies: Sweden and Austria, 2016 [2]">{{cite news |title=A Milli Takımı'nın Aday Kadrosu Açıkandı |url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/a-milli-futbol-takimi-nin-aday---2212072-skorerhaber/ |publisher=[[Milliyet]] |date=18 March 2016 |accessdate=19 March 2016 |language=Turkish |archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl=no}}</ref>
Substituting [[Ozan Tufan]] in the dying minutes of friendly game against Sweden, Söyüncü earned his first senior national team cap on 24 March 2016, Thursday.<ref name="Friendlies: Sweden and Austria, 2016 [3]">{{cite news |title=Türkiye 2–1 İsveç |url=http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=24764 |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation|TFF]] |date=24 March 2016 |accessdate=24 March 2016 |language=Turkish |archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl=no}}</ref> Earning his 2nd cap, he was on starting line-up at friendly with [[Russia national football team|Russia]] on 1 September 2016, ended 0–0.<ref name="Turkey - Russia friendly">{{cite news |title=Türkiye – Rusya: 0–0 |url=http://www.ntv.com.tr/spor/turkiye-rusya-0-0,qjgdRrXD3UmaJeICuXggKA |publisher=[[NTV Spor]] |date=1 September 2016 |accessdate=8 October 2016 |language=Turkish |archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl=no}}</ref>
==Style of play== Possessing leadership attributes, Söyüncü is good at playmaking, dribbling and timing.<ref name="Four Four Two Turkish Edition">{{cite web |url=http://fourfourtwo.com.tr/2015/11/16/bu-cocukta-is-var-caglar-soyuncu-altinordu/ |title=Bu çocukta iş var: Çağlar Söyüncü (Altınordu) |publisher=[[Four Four Two|Four Four Two Turkish Edition]] |author= |date=16 November 2015 |accessdate=22 March 2016 |language=tr}}</ref> Standing at 1.87 m, he is strong in the air.<ref name="Four Four Two Turkish Edition"/> In 2016, he stated that his idol is Spaniard defender [[Carles Puyol]] and he admires German international [[Mats Hummels]].<ref name="Admiration: Puyol and Hummels">{{cite news |title=A Milli Takımı'nın Aday Kadrosu Açıkandı |url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/caglar-soyuncu-bundesliga-nin---2241436-skorerhaber/ |publisher=[[Milliyet]] |date=8 May 2016 |accessdate=8 October 2016 |language=Turkish |archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl=no}}</ref>
