{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}} {{Use British English|date=May 2016}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Hamza Choudhury | image = | image_size = | caption = | fullname = Hamza Dewan Choudhury<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/-/media/files/thefaportal/governance-docs/registrations/player-registration---august-2016.ashx |title=List of temporary transfers of players under written contract between 01/08/2016 and 31/08/2016 |publisher=The Football Association |format=PDF |page=24 |accessdate=11 February 2018}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1997|10|1|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Loughborough]], England | height = {{convert|1.78|m|order=flip}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lcfc.com/players/13248/Hamza-Choudhury/profile |title=Hamza Choudhury |publisher=Leicester City F.C. |accessdate=22 December 2018}}</ref> | position = [[Midfielder]] | currentclub = [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] | clubnumber = 38 | youthyears1 = 2011–2015 | youthclubs1 = [[Leicester City F.C. Reserves and Academy|Leicester City]] | years1 = 2015– | clubs1 = [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] | caps1 = 13 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2016 | clubs2 = → [[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]] (loan) | caps2 = 13 | goals2 = 0 | years3 = 2016–2017 | clubs3 = → [[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]] (loan) | caps3 = 13 | goals3 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2018– | nationalteam1 = [[England national under-21 football team|England U21]] | nationalcaps1 = 4 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | club-update = 00:01, 31 January 2019 (UTC) }} '''Hamza Dewan Choudhury''' (born 1 October 1997) is an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].
==Club career== Choudhury began his career at the [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] [[Leicester City F.C. Reserves and Academy|Academy]], and at the age of 16 was reportedly monitored by a number of top European clubs.<ref>{{cite news |title=Transfer news: Leicester City youngster Hamza Choudhury attracting European interest |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11712/9488982/transfer-news-leicester-city-youngster-hamza-choudhury-attracting-interest |accessdate=12 March 2016 |work=Sky Sports |date=25 September 2014}}</ref> He joined [[Football League One|League One]] leaders [[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]] on a one-month loan deal on 27 February 2016.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wilkinson |first1=Ashley |title=Burton Albion transfer news: Leicester City youngster Hamza Choudhury signs on loan |url=http://www.burtonmail.co.uk/Burton-Albion-transfer-news-Leicester-City/story-28819588-detail/story.html |accessdate=12 March 2016 |work=Burton Mail |date=27 February 2016}}</ref> He made his debut in [[the Football League]] later that same day, coming on as a 77th-minute substitute for [[Tom Naylor]] in a 0–0 draw with [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]] at the [[Pirelli Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Burton's lead at the top of League One was cut to two points after they were held by fellow high-flyers Walsall |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/35618946 |accessdate=12 March 2016 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |date=27 February 2016}}</ref> On 6 August 2016, Choudhury signed another loan deal with [[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]] for the 2016–17 season.<ref>{{cite news |title=Hamza Choudhury re-signs on loan |url=http://www.burtonalbionfc.co.uk/news/article/2016-17/hamza-choudhury-re-signs-on-loan-3229040.aspx |date=6 August 2016}}</ref> On the same day, Choudhury featured in Burton Albion's first ever [[Football League Championship]] game, claiming an assist in a 4–3 defeat against [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Forest: On the whistle match report |url=http://www.burtonalbionfc.co.uk/news/article/2016-17/forest-on-the-whistle-match-report-3229562.aspx |accessdate=6 August 2016 |work=[[Burton Albion F.C.]] |date=6 August 2016}}</ref>
On 19 September 2017, Choudhury debuted for Leicester City coming on as substitute in the 82nd minute of a [[EFL Cup]] 3rd round home win against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Carabao Cup: Leicester City vs Liverpool – 2:0 |url=https://www.lcfc.com/match/24403#latest |date=19 September 2017}}</ref> On 28 November 2017, Choudhury made his [[Premier League]] debut for Leicester coming on as substitute in the 83rd minute of a home win against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Premier League: Leicester City vs Tottenham Hotspur – 2:1 |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42061046 |date=28 November 2017}}</ref> His first Premier League start came on 14 April 2018, in a 2–1 away defeat to [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Burnley 2–1 Leicester City |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43678367 |accessdate=14 April 2018 |work=BBC Sport |date=14 April 2018}}</ref>
==International career== On 26 May 2018, Choudhury made his debut for the [[England national under-21 football team]], coming on as a substitute during the 2–1 win against China under-21 in the [[2018 Toulon Tournament]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Choudhury makes maiden England u21s appearance |accessdate=27 May 2018 |date=27 May 2018 |work=Leicester City Football Club |url=https://www.lcfc.com/news/694196/choudhury-makes-maiden-england-u21s-appearance}}</ref> Choudhury started for England in the next match of the tournament, a 0–0 draw against Mexico.<ref>{{cite news |title=England U21S 0 Mexico U21S 0: Young Lions remain on course for Toulon Tournament semis despite stalemate |accessdate=31 May 2018 |date=29 May 2018 |url=https://www.thesun.co.uk/sport/football/6406270/england-u21s-0-mexico-u21s-0-toulon-tournament/}}</ref>
==Personal life== Choudhury's father is Grenadian and his mother is of [[British Bangladeshi|Bangladeshi]] descent. Regarding his ethnicity Hamza has stated: "Both my parents are Bangladeshi and I have been brought up in an Asian family, but I have Caribbean blood in me as my dad is from Grenada. We have a massive family".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tanner |first1=Rob |title=Why Leicester City's local lad Hamza Choudhury really stands out |url=http://www.leicestermercury.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/leicester-citys-local-lad-hamza-613829 |work=Leicester Mercury |accessdate=28 November 2017 |date=12 October 2017}}</ref><ref name="bbpower-inspiration16">{{cite book |last=Qureshi |first=Ayesha |title=British Bangladeshi Power & Inspiration |url=http://www.bbpower-inspiration.com/archives/portfolio-item/bbpi |date=January 2016 |publisher=British Bangla Media Group |page=31 |isbn= |accessdate=1 June 2017}}</ref>
